        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 1:29PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 129 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Monument, or 18 miles north of Colorado Springs, moving southeast at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monument, Air Force Academy, Palmer Lake, and Gleneagle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
